fields.educationPolicyResponsibilityMixedText: The first confirmed case of COVID-19 in Guinea-Bissau was registered on March 24th, by July 6 there were 1,765 confirmed cases and 25 deaths.  By this time, the pandemic was being managed by an Interministerial Commission, under the authority of the Prime Minister, with technical support from the Center for Emergency Health Operations (COES).  In view of the rapid expansion of the number of cases, with Guinea-Bissau being the 6th most affected country in the ECOWAS region and the 17th in Africa, it was decided to create a High Commissioner for Response to COVID-19, installed in the Office of the President of the Republic (PR), with full authority to lead, coordinate, direct and manage Guinea-Bissau's response to the COVID-19 pandemic. The education policies responding to the COVID-19 pandemic are developed by the Ministries of National Education and Higher Education with the support of the development partners.
